content: I love this app! I'm still learning to read music and this really helps me to practise, in a fun way. The app did have a problem with start up, but when I sent them an email, they were amazing about it, and fixed it within a week. Their support was amazing, and they even sent back an email to ask if it had worked. I just wished they made more apps!
I tried to download it on my Galaxy Note 20 Ultra 5G Android and it didn't work. I did get my refund back. I suppose it's not for Android Phones.

I had the iPhone version and I could practice transposition because you played the notes on your instrument to clear them in the game.  As a french horn player this was a valuable way to get fast at my transposition in a short amount of time.  I got an android phone and I'm upset this is not the same game across devices. If it were I'd give it 5 stars and pay money to have it.

I loved the program when it was online only. I geeked out when I saw it was on the apple store. I was bummed when I saw it wasn't on Google Play. But fear not, after an email to Mr. Gonci, it was on the Play store WITHIN HOURS!   About the game, it allows you to pick your range of notes and staff then it scrolls a note across the screen you must zap by clicking the correct letter name. Every 10 correct, you gain a level and it gets faster! Be quick and correct because you only have 3 lives!
